medical_history.chief_complaint: Acute onset right upper quadrant abdominal pain.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms started at midnight, with the patient developing nausea and vomiting approximately 10 times. Initial emesis was brown/bilious, later becoming clear. The patient had a meal consisting of crackers/dip and apple pie a few hours prior to the onset of pain. RUQ pain persisted leading to her presentation for medical attention.
medical_history.family_history: Mother and maternal grandmother underwent cholecystectomy. Paternal grandmother had a brain tumor. Maternal grandmother had lung cancer. Father's family has a history of cardiac disease.
